<rss version="2.0"><channel><title>GitHub Trending: Smalltalk, This week</title><link>https://github.com/trending/smalltalk?since=weekly</link><description>The top repositories on GitHub for smalltalk, measured weekly</description><pubDate>Mon, 20 Jan 2020 01:06:13 GMT</pubDate><lastBuildDate>Mon, 20 Jan 2020 01:06:13 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>PyRSS2Gen-1.1.0</generator><docs>http://blogs.law.harvard.edu/tech/rss</docs><ttl>720</ttl><item><title>pharo-spec/Spec #1 in Smalltalk, This week</title><link>https://github.com/pharo-spec/Spec</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;[No description found.]&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;No README was found for this project.&lt;/p&gt;</description><author>pharo-spec</author><guid isPermaLink="false">https://github.com/pharo-spec/Spec</guid><pubDate>Mon, 20 Jan 2020 00:01:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>pharo-spec/Commander2 #2 in Smalltalk, This week</title><link>https://github.com/pharo-spec/Commander2</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;Flexible implementation of the command design pattern.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div id="readme" class="md" data-path="README.md"&gt;&lt;article class="markdown-body entry-content p-5" itemprop="text"&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;a id="user-content-commander-2" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#commander-2"&gt;&lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Commander 2&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://travis-ci.org/pharo-spec/Commander2" rel="nofollow"&gt;&lt;img src="https://camo.githubusercontent.com/0a66474f180586bd6bcc76361c82bcce1ac1564b/68747470733a2f2f7472617669732d63692e6f72672f706861726f2d737065632f436f6d6d616e646572322e7376673f6272616e63683d6d6173746572" alt="Build Status" data-canonical-src="https://travis-ci.org/pharo-spec/Commander2.svg?branch=master" style="max-width:100%;"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a href="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PolyMathOrg/DataFrame/master/LICENSE" rel="nofollow"&gt;&lt;img src="https://camo.githubusercontent.com/890acbdcb87868b382af9a4b1fac507b9659d9bf/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f62616467652f6c6963656e73652d4d49542d626c75652e737667" alt="License" data-canonical-src="https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-blue.svg" style="max-width:100%;"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a href="https://pharo.org/download" rel="nofollow"&gt;&lt;img src="https://camo.githubusercontent.com/bc612a3bd4297906992550a0e6e485ea6e13fe40/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f62616467652f506861726f2d382e302d2532336161633966662e737667" alt="Pharo version" data-canonical-src="https://img.shields.io/badge/Pharo-8.0-%23aac9ff.svg" style="max-width:100%;"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Implementation of the command design pattern with the following objectives:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Simple model of commands&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ease reusability of commands accross multiple tools / framework&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Instance of commands can be modified (e.g., name, description, etc...)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pluging custom user-command made easy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a id="user-content-install" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#install"&gt;&lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Install&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight highlight-source-smalltalk"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class="pl-c1"&gt;Metacello&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="pl-k"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;span class="pl-c1"&gt;repository:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="pl-s"&gt;&lt;span class="pl-pds"&gt;'&lt;/span&gt;github://pharo-spec/Commander2/src&lt;span class="pl-pds"&gt;'&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;;
	&lt;span class="pl-c1"&gt;baseline:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="pl-s"&gt;&lt;span class="pl-pds"&gt;'&lt;/span&gt;Commander2&lt;span class="pl-pds"&gt;'&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;;
	load&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a id="user-content-example" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#example"&gt;&lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Example&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Note: This example is now shipped with the Spec2 integration which is managed by &lt;a href="https://github.com/pharo-spec/Spec"&gt;Spec2 project&lt;/a&gt;.
The code is thus no longer available in this repository.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;Commander2-ContactBook&lt;/code&gt; package contains an example of Commander2 usage in the context of a Spec application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The following code should be checked when learning how to use the framework:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;CmContactBookCommand&lt;/code&gt; and subclasses are the definition of commands required by the example application.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;CmContactBookPresenter class&amp;gt;&amp;gt;#buildCommandsGroupWith:forRoot:&lt;/code&gt; This method is the entry point to describe commands available to your Spec presenter. One can learn how to build group of commands from this method.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;CmContactBookPresenter&amp;gt;&amp;gt;#initializeWidgets&lt;/code&gt; This method shows how to inject a Spec's &lt;code&gt;MenuPresenter&lt;/code&gt; built from a command group in your presenter.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;CmContactBookPresenter&amp;gt;&amp;gt;#initializeWindow:&lt;/code&gt; This method shows how to bind the shortcuts defined by your command group to your Spec presenter.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/article&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><author>pharo-spec</author><guid isPermaLink="false">https://github.com/pharo-spec/Commander2</guid><pubDate>Mon, 20 Jan 2020 00:02:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>feenkcom/gtoolkit-examples #3 in Smalltalk, This week</title><link>https://github.com/feenkcom/gtoolkit-examples</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;[No description found.]&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;No README was found for this project.&lt;/p&gt;</description><author>feenkcom</author><guid isPermaLink="false">https://github.com/feenkcom/gtoolkit-examples</guid><pubDate>Mon, 20 Jan 2020 00:03:00 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>